  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cook the sushi or jasmine rice following pack instructions."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, smash the garlic until flattened, then remove the skins. Slice the ginger into thin, round discs and set aside on a plate."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Combine the sauce ingredients in a small bowl and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Chop the chicken into bite-sized chunks and pat dry with kitchen paper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the neutral oil in a medium-sized casserole dish or wok. Cook the garlic and ginger for 1-2 mins or until lightly golden."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Push the garlic and ginger to the side, then add the chicken (laying it as flat as possible) and cook for 1 min each side, or until lightly golden."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Now add the sauce and toss well. Add a bit of water, so it’s only one-quarter of the way up the chicken, then bring to a simmer and add a lid. Reduce the heat to the lowest setting and cook for 25 mins, stirring halfway through."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, slice the red pepper, onion, spring onions and chilli into bite-sized pieces. Tear the basil leaves and set everything aside on a large plate."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Remove the lid and bring to the boil, then toss in all the chopped veg. Toss for 2 mins, then add the basil and turn the heat off."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finish with a drizzle of sesame oil and toasted sesame seeds, then serve over the rice. Alternatively, grab a small pot that will hold all the rice (or individual clay pots) and set it/them over a medium heat. Add 1 tbsp sesame oil to the pot(s) and all the cooked rice, tip the chicken and sauce on top and cover with a lid. Cook for 2-3 mins to crisp-up the base of the rice. Then serve inside the pots"
    }
  ],
